description:
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen in North Durham EIP for an experienced professional from a social work, nursing or occupational therapy background to join a busy community team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be expected to complete specific EIP assessments for clients who have been referred to North Durham Early Intervention in Psychosis, in line with the referral to treatment time standard.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to be enthusiastic and highly motivated with experience in delivery of assessments and sign posting of care. You will support service users in their recovery working both autonomously and as part of a team. As Assessment Clinician you will be expected to supervise and mentor junior members of the team as well as students.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder is required to travel independently and a lease car scheme is in operation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Michael Colledge, Team Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;michaeljohn.colledge@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;0191 3336011&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;or Karen Winship, Advanced Practitioner&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;0191 3336011&lt;/p&gt;
